ol and offers an East-West dialogue that enriches our understanding of Japanese thought while also shedding light on our own assumptions, habits of thought, and prejudices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aNothing (Philosophy). 0aPhilosophy, Japanesex20th century. 0aPhilosophy, Japanesey20th century. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Buddhism. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aRELIGION / Philosophy.2bisacsh1 aKasulis, Thomas P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438445434423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438445434/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles